org.jawin.marshal
Class GenericStub

java.lang.Object
  org.jawin.marshal.GenericStub
public class GenericStub
extends java.lang.Object

GenericStub methods for calling generic native DLL entry point (ie. entry points not matching signatures in SharedStubs), and COM vtable and IDispatch based objects. These methods should usually NOT be called directly, instead use the methods in FuncPtr, COMPtr or DispatchPtr.

The native implementations of the methods in this class are in GenericStub.cpp.

Version:
$Revision: 1.5 $
Author:
Stuart Halloway, http://www.relevancellc.com/halloway/weblog/
See Also:
FuncPtr, COMPtr, DispatchPtr

dispatchInvoke

public static byte[] dispatchInvoke(java.lang.String instructions,
                                    int stackSize,
                                    int argStreamSize,
                                    byte[] argStream,
                                    java.lang.String meth,
                                    DispatchConstants flags,
                                    int peer,
                                    int unknown)
                             throws COMException
for making a native IDispatch method-call. Should usually NOT be called directly, instead use one of the invoke, get or put methods in DispatchPtr.

Important: the dispatch invoke marshal arguments rigth to left. This is the case for both the instructions string (both the in and out part) and for the argStream byte array. Please see the implementation in DispatchPtr.invokeN() for an example of how this should be done.

COM always uses ReturnFlags.CHECK_HRESULT for error-checking.

Throws:
COMException
See Also:
DispatchPtr.invoke(), DispatchPtr.get(), DispatchPtr.put()
